================================================================================
TCS NQT REASONING ABILITY EXAM BLUEPRINT & TOPIC PRIORITY
Prepared by: TCS Senior Tester (10+ Years Experience)
Target Time-per-Question: 60 Seconds Benchmark
================================================================================

TCS NQT Reasoning Ability is where candidates often lose their momentum. TCS builds
complex puzzles and critical reasoning arguments that seem easy but have highly deceptive
trap options. Your success relies on identifying high-ROI structural patterns quickly.

THE CORE STRATEGY: Treat coding, series, and directions as quick wins (under 45 seconds).
Save your cognitive energy for critical reasoning and data arrangement puzzles.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟥 TIER 1: HIGH FREQUENCY & SPEED-SOLVING ACCELERATORS (Must Master First)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These topics form the core chunk of the foundational section. If you learn the structural rules
and notation tricks, you can consistently crack these in under 45-60 seconds.

1. Coding Decoding
   - Subtopics: Letter shifting, operational coding, matrix/fictional language coding
   - Weightage: High (2-3 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (35 - 50 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Never solve by writing the alphabet in real time. Memorize the A-Z forward/reverse
     positions using the EJOTY (5, 10, 15, 20, 25) framework to spot shifting patterns instantly.

2. Letter Series & Number Series (Identifying Word & Numeric Pattern)
   - Subtopics: Missing terms, wrong term in series, alphanumeric combinations
   - Weightage: High (2-3 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy to Moderate (30 - 55 seconds)
   - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: If the logic doesn't jump out in 30 seconds, don't stare at it.
     TCS loves hidden double-layer differences (prime numbers, alternating cubes/squares). Calculate the
     differences first.

3. Syllogism
   - Subtopics: 2-3 statements with conditions (Some, All, No, Only a few)
   - Weightage: High (2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (40 - 50 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Master the standard Venn Diagram approach. Pay extreme attention to "Only a few"
     and "Possibility" cases, which are standard testing boundaries for Advanced eligibility.

4. Directions
   - Subtopics: Degree-based turns, shadow problems, shortest distance (Pythagoras theorem)
   - Weightage: High (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (40 - 55 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Don't redraw the full map for simple turning questions. Track net degree rotations
     (Clockwise vs Counter-Clockwise) or net cardinal coordinate movements algebraically.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟨 TIER 2: HIGH WEIGHTAGE CRITICAL & ANALYSIS MODULES (The Digital/Prime Filter)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TCS relies heavily on verbal logic and analytical evaluation. These can be solved quickly if
you maintain complete objectivity and avoid personal bias.

5. Logical Deduction / Critical Reasoning
   - Subtopics: Statements & Assumptions, Statements & Conclusions, Statements & Arguments, Statements & Course of Actions
   - Weightage: High (3-4 Questions total)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (45 - 65 seconds)
   - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: The biggest mistake is using external real-world knowledge.
     Treat the given statement as absolute truth. Assumptions must be implicitly necessary, while
     conclusions must be 100% logically certain.

6. Data Sufficiency
   - Subtopics: Math or logic base evaluation using Statement I & Statement II
   - Weightage: High (2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (50 - 70 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: Stop calculating the final answer! Your only job is to determine if the data is enough.
     Check Statement I independently, Statement II independently, and then combine only if both fail.

7. Blood Relation
   - Subtopics: Coded blood relations (A + B means A is father of B), family tree diagrams
   - Weightage: Moderate to High (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (45 - 60 seconds)
   - The Shortcut: For coded blood relations, use Gender Elimination and Generation Gap counting.
     If the question asks for a male relationship, eliminate options where the person's final symbol forces a female gender.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🟦 TIER 3: PATTERN RECOGNITION & VISUAL GEOMETRY (Moderate Priority)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These check spatial perception and raw structural observation. They are clean marks if you work systematically.

8. Visual / Spatial Reasoning & Pattern Recognition (Figure & Factual Analysis)
   - Subtopics: Figure completion, embedded figures, next figure in series
   - Weightage: Moderate (2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy to Moderate (40 - 60 seconds)
   - The Strategy: Focus on a single element (like an arrow, dot, or shading) and track its behavior
     (e.g., 90-degree clockwise rotation). Do not try to look at the full figure all at once.

9. Cuts & Unfolds & Unboxing a Cube/Dice
   - Subtopics: Paper folding/cutting patterns, opposite faces of open dice
   - Weightage: Moderate (1-2 Questions)
   - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate (45 - 60 seconds)
   - The Trick: For dice unboxing, remember that faces separated by exactly one block are always opposites.
     Use the alternate block rule to eliminate impossible folded orientations instantly.

10. Venn Diagrams
    - Subtopics: Logical relationship matching, geometrical region intersections
    - Weightage: Moderate (1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Easy (30 - 45 seconds)
    - The Strategy: Highly logical and visual. Move step-by-step from the outermost classification inward.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
⬛ TIER 4: HIGH-RISK TIME CONSUMERS (Save for Last or Advanced Clearance)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These items can easily kill 2 to 3 minutes if you don't keep tabs on your pacing. Practice them to
learn rapid elimination cues.

11. Seating Arrangement & Data Arrangement
    - Subtopics: Linear rows, circular facing inwards/outwards, tabular scheduling
    - Weightage: Moderate to High (2 Questions, often linked to 1-2 caselets)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Hard (75 - 120 seconds)
    - TCS Internal Insight / Trap to Avoid: These are massive traps in the Foundation section.
      Always construct parallel possibilities simultaneously rather than trying to guess one configuration
      and restarting if it fails.

12. Decision Making & Attention to Detail
    - Subtopics: Recruitment criteria filters, eligibility condition checking
    - Weightage: Moderate (1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Hard (60 - 90 seconds due to heavy text volume)
    - The Strategy: Create a quick checklist layout on your scratchpad with criteria metrics
      (Age, Experience, Marks) and check the candidate details systematically against it.

13. Clocks and Calendar
    - Subtopics: Date matching, leap year odd days, faulty clock tracking
    - Weightage: Low (0-1 Question)
    - Solvability in 60 Sec: Moderate to Hard (60 - 80 seconds)
    - Note: Shared overlapping weightage with the Quantitative section. Stick to modular arithmetic for calendars.

